726589f-c.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Onderdonk Avenue
726589f-c.text:
Flushing Avenue, east side, south of Onderdonk Avenue,
showing in order the Onderdonk, Covert-Jenkins and Peter Wyokoff
houses. The house in the foreground is No. 1416 Flushing Avenue.
This is a set of four views. See others for more data. Also see
the New York Sun, February 18, 1939.
1922.
Views 1,2 and 3.
View 4: September 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726582f-b.title: Queens: Flushing Avenue - Onderdonk Avenue
726582f-b.text:
1416 Flushing Ave. (in front of house seen in foreground), between
Onderdonk Ave. (right unpaved) and Senesa.Awe.; showing in a set of
three views the rear of the Onderdonk-Schoomaker house. Mrs. Ann Onderdonk
and her heirs were the owners from 1852-1869. View No. 2 also shows ships
on Newtown Creek. View No. 3 shows a 5-story building of the Steel and
Tube Inc. of New York in Eings County. The right background is in Queens
County. Fore more data see the N.Y. Sun, February 18, 1939.
1922.
Views 1 \& 2.
View 3: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
